posts.title: Using social media, e-mail marketing and SEO to drive massive traffic to your site
posts.text:
The success of any site is dependent on the amount of traffic or visitors it can attract. Getting traffic is a fundamental problem of most website because they lack popularity. Experts say the surest way to gain popularity online and drive good traffic to your site is by posting exclusive contents. 
Getting traffic solely on content basis is a herculean task because it requires hard work, perseverance, consistency, determination, focus and writing articles that are solution oriented. Once you can proffer solutions to problems people go online in search of, go to sleep, your traffic is assured. An easier approach to gaining traffic would be through: ·          Social media campaign ·          Email marketing ·          Search engine optimization (SEO) 1.       Social media campaign: Having a very strong presence on the various social media sites like facebook, twitter, linkedin, tagged, pinterest, instagram, etc can drive massive loads of traffic to your site. Endeavor to add their share buttons to the footer segment of your site. A hit on these share buttons delivers your new contents to your various social media profile so that family and sfriends can view your posts. Also, there are automated delivery engines that can also deliver your contents to your various social media profile automatically in seconds. Sites like dlvr.it, twitterfeed.com, networkblogs.com, onlywire.com, rss graffiti on facebook, ifttt.com, hootsuites.com, etc are very good automated delivery sites to try out. 2.       Email marketing: Use emails to popularize your site by creating a mailing list of your subscribers. Updates on your site are sent via emails to contacts on your mailing list. With this, subscribers to your site can have access to your site directly from their mail box. Hence by so doing massive loads of traffic is driven to your website. Mailchimp is a very good site for incorporating subscription form into your website. 3.       Search Engine Optimization (SEO): Optimize the potentials search engines to drive massive loads of traffic to your site. Get your site indexed by Google and Bing webmaster tool so that it becomes visible and discoverable in Google and Bing searches. This avails your site the opportunity to be crawled which in turn drives traffic to the site.

posts.title: Egypt's Sisi Rules Out Extending Presidential Term
posts.text:
Egypt's President Abdel Fattah al-Sisi ruled out a constitutional amendment to extend his term, saying an election would be held next year and he will not run again in 2022, in an interview with CNBC Monday.
Sisi is a former army chief who overthrew his Islamist predecessor in 2013 and won an election a year later.
Some of his supporters including a member of parliament want to allow Sisi to stay longer in office by extending the time between elections and removing the two four-year-term limit.
But Sisi said elections will take place as scheduled in March or April 2018 and he would not ask for a constitutional amendment.
Sisi did not say he would run again but the former field marshal is expected to stand and win in another landslide in the absence of any serious opposition.
"I'm with preserving two four year terms and not to change it," he told the American broadcaster.
"I'm not for any amendments to be made to the constitution in this period," he added.
Sisi won the 2014 election with about 97 percent of the vote. His only opponent, Hamdeen Sabahi, received less votes than spoiled ballots.
The president is popular among many Egyptians who say the country needs a firm hand following years up tumult that battered the economy.
But he has faced mounting criticism over a crackdown on Islamist and secular opponents and what rights groups say are increasingly repressive measures to stifle dissent.
So far only one opponent, lawyer and dissident Khaled Ali, has announced his candidacy for the 2018 election.
Ali, who challenged an unpopular government deal to hand over two Red Sea islands to Saudi Arabia, had run in the 2012 election that brought Islamist president Mohamed Morsi to power.
He received less than one percent of the vote then.

荣耀将在10月11日推出一款全面屏机型荣耀7X，这是自麦芒6、Mate 10之后的又一款全面屏手机，可以看出在紧追全面屏这条路上， 荣耀7x 华为表现的很是积极。
之前官方预热过这款荣耀7X，现在又来了一记神助攻，曝光了这款新机的信息。
从曝光的荣耀7X真机照来看，这款新机将配备5.93英寸屏幕，18：9的全面屏设计，分辨率为2160×1080像素。手机背部为金属材质，三段式设计，指纹识别放在背面上部中央位置、横排双摄。
配置方面，荣耀7X搭载的应该是麒麟659处理器，主频2.36GHz，后置主摄像头是1200万像素+200万像素双摄组合，前置800万像素，内置3240mAh容量电池，搭载Android 7.0系统。
至于内存组合上，从之前网友曝光的荣耀7X发布会PPT照片来看，应该有两个版本，3GB+64GB版、4GB+64GB版。
至于售价，荣耀7X的3GB+64GB版定价1799元，4GB+64GB版定价2099元，从售价来看，荣耀7X很有可能属于荣耀品牌比较低端的畅玩系列，主要是以小米5X、魅蓝Note6等为对手。不管怎么说，这款手机的性价比还是非常不错的。

posts.title: President appoints Champika, Amunugama and Anura to solve petrol crisis
posts.text: 39 President appoints Champika, Amunugama and Anura to solve petrol crisis 59 Views President Maithripala Sirisena has appointed a Cabinet sub-committee comprising of Ministers Patali Champika Ranawaka, Dr. Sarath Amunugama, and Anura Priyadharshana Yapa to quickly solve the petrol crisis. The President has also instructed to import petrol stocks from India to ease the shortage. Although supplies have been increased, long queues could still be seen outside most of the fuel stations in many parts of the country. During the last two days, 4,800MT of petrol have been issued to fuel sheds island-wide. Our correspondents stated that the supply of petrol has been restricted to Rs. 1000 per car and Rs. 500 per motorcycle. The Ministry of Petroleum Resources Development, however, stated that it has not instructed any petrol station owner to limit the amounts of petrol to be pumped per vehicle. Meanwhile, it has been reported that cab operators have increased the fares as a result of the prevailing petrol shortage.The prevailing petrol crisis was also discussed in Parliament today (07). Here, Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe revealed 2 petrol shipments will arrive on the island tomorrow and day after.He added then the prevailing issue will be normalized.Meanwhile, speaking here, Minister Arjuna Ranatunga said he's being influenced to release a substandard fuel shipment imported by Lanka IOC.He said he will not authorize the release, despite he's pressurized to do so.

posts.text:
By Timothy Olson 

Learning how to defend yourself is a great way to keep yourself safe. There are many ways to do this. You can watch self-help videos from home and teach yourself. Alternatively, you can take some classes that you teach you how to do this. The martial arts center toledo Ohio offers is a great place for children to learn how to defend themselves and also keep busy.

If your child is active and enjoys the sport, this could be just for them. It is a great way for your little spark to use their energy and also learn a new art form as well. It is not for everyone and if your child does not have an active tendency, then you should not enroll them in these classes.

Tese classes are designed to teach children discipline. The skills they learn also allows them to defend themselves when they are in trouble or attacked by a stranger. So this is a great activity for kids to get into. It is also a much more constructive use of their time than playing games online.

These classes are held in various destinations. However, the art itself comes from Asian countries. It is an ancient art and is respected and used by people all over the world. Not so much for its self-defense benefits, but also for its discipline that gets instilled in you when you do it.

It is said that children learn the most amount of information when they are very young. Children ages of 0 to 5 years absorb the most amount of information growing up. So it does make sense to introduce children to things such as martial arts and as young as possible. Sooner just sounds better than later.

This is one of the best things that a child can do with their time. They can choose to do other things like playing video games and so on, but this is a good old-fashioned use of their times. It is a great way of enabling children to be better in every way. They need self-discipline and this can teach it to them.

There are many facilities offering this service. You just need to make sure that you choose one where there are children of similar age groups and you feel comfortable with. So this is all that matters when you are placing your kids there. There are always things you can learn from this if you really want to.

All in all this is a great activity for children of all ages. Smaller children may be better off starting as early as possible. Older children should also not give up hope as they can still learn all they can. They may not be as fast at learning as the younger ones, but they will absorb the info nonetheless. So why not offer the chance irrespective of whether you think they can do it or not. There is only one way to really find out what your child is made of. Try this you will soon come to know what they are all about.

posts.title: We are recruiting!
posts.text:
We are recruiting new members for the regional section of the International Society for Computational Biology (ISCB) Student Council (SC). Join us for a short discussion if you are interested in participating in our organisation. To keep it brief, we summarized various questions you might have below.
Where and when? On the 14th November at the foyer of the Genopode building (close to the UNIL-Sorge metro station) from 17:30 to 19:00. 
What do we do? We are organising various types of events to enhance the scientific exchange and communicate science to various audiences with focus on bioinformatics. Especially, our aim is to strengthen the scientific network between PhDs, postdocs and PIs. What do we need? We are looking for active and interested people that are willing to help in their spare time with various organisational tasks. The only thing required is to be open and constructive. Who are we? We are PhD students and postdocs from UNIL and EPFL , covering a broad range of cultural backgrounds and scientific expertise in bioinformatics. We also welcome Master students. What does it bring you? Scientific exchange, communication and organisational skills are increasingly important in a scientific career and joining our organisation will help you to get hands on experience. In 2019, Basel will host the ECCB/ISCB conference. As part of this event we will play a major role as the local representation of ISCB student council. This will be a great opportunity for you to be included in the organization of a major conference. If you are interested in more details about past events and our structure, please check our website or our facebook page . Best Regards, On behalf of the committee, Amel Bekkar
